  "original_title": "\u0dad\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dad\u0dc0\u0dcf\u0daf\u0dd3 \u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dc4\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca \u0db4\u0dd2\u0dc5\u0dd2\u0db6\u0db3 \u0dbd\u0dd2\u0db4\u0dd2\u0dba \u0d9c\u0dd0\u0db1 \u0d9a\u0dbd\u0db6\u0dbd \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0d91\u0db4\u0dcf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Don't worry about the article about a terrorist attack",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Ministry of Defense has issued a statement saying not to panic over the letter submitted by the Inspector General of Police to the Secretary of Defense stating information about a terrorist attack.",
        "The Ministry of Defense says that the revelation of a terrorist attack which is said to be possible on the 5th and 6th of this month by highlighting 'Black July' in the article which is currently circulating in the social media is based on unconfirmed information received through the intelligence agencies.",
        "This information is unconfirmed information by the intelligence agencies and as mentioned in the article, no ground information has been received about the possibility of a terrorist attack highlighting 'Black July'.",
        "Further, these attacks may be carried out by terrorist groups and various anti-government groups may incite violence to discredit and destabilize the government.",
        "Further investigations are currently being conducted on this intelligence information and the Ministry of Defense further requests the public not to worry and engage in their daily activities without worrying that all measures have been taken to establish a high level of security."
      ],
